name: Happy Hawkers

reviews.text: Tried the mee rubus and longtong, ordered via Grab. Both were super yummy! Apology for the photo as i decided to review when my food is almost finished. Definitely will visit the stall one day. Ps: they were from a chinese stall therefore it might not be halal.
Great food. Maggi goreng with sunny side egg. Maggi was not clump together and the egg was runny. Portion was big. All for $5.

Best Kuching Laksa!! I've been following them since their 1st stall (Tasty Sarawak Kolo Mee) at 267A Toh Guan (re-open 23/4/25), Bt Panjang, Woodlands then now at Bt Batok (moved).
Laksa is authentic, soup is so yummy with big prawns.
They are also at Bt Merah, Raffles City, Shaw House and Sun Plaza.
*** 22 Dec 2023 NEW location = Yew Tee Point Koufu (Basement 1)
Clean and bright coffee shop.  First time eatimg from.this mixed veg stall. Surprised that you can still get Kopi o at s$1 for fairly new coffeeshop.  The gigantic fan makes it more cooling.

Bought a big bao from the dimsum stall
Home. First bite got a sour taste. Don’t taste normal. After few hours had vomit and sick. Don’t ever patron this stall. Saw a review below mentioning the same.
